.TH PVESH-MOCK 1 "June 2026" "Version 0.1.0" "PVE SAN Fenced Tools"
.SH NAME
pvesh-mock \- Mock pvesh CLI command for testing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pvesh-mock
[\fB\-\-output\-format\fR \fIformat\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR | \fB\-\-verbose\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
\fIPATH\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pvesh-mock
is a mock tool designed to simulate the Proxmox VE \fBpvesh\fR command-line utility. It parses the commands (such as \fBls\fR or \fBget\fR) and target paths, and returns mock test data from JSON files located in a test data directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-o ", " \-\-output\-format " format"
Format of the output. Default is "json".
.TP
.B \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging/output.
.SH POSITIONALS
.TP
.I COMMAND
The query command (e.g., ls, get).
.TP
.I PATH
The API path to query (e.g., /nodes/pve001/qemu).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PVE_SAN_TEST_DATA_DIR
Custom directory path to load test JSON configuration files from. If not specified, defaults to "test-data/pvesh".
.SH AUTHOR
Bernd Zeimetz <bernd@bzed.de>
